title: GoPro Music: Matt and Kim’s GoPro Catapults Into Crowd at Governors Ball 2016
description:
For Matt and Kim’s latest music video, they used a wooden coat hanger, some fishing wire, and a GoPro filming 720p at 240 frames per second. The result: a circular moment frozen in time. Watch them take the rig to the stage at Governors Ball 2016 with a little help from Curt from Flosstradamus. The wire didn’t hold up and we get an up-close and personal look at the NYC crowd! 

Shot 100% on the HERO4® camera 

MUSIC:
Matt and Kim - "Please No More" 
from the new EP - WE WERE THE WEIRDOS 

Matt and Kim's new music video, "Let's Run Away", shot in the same style

WE WERE THE WEIRDOS
